<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-06-03T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-06-03T03:00:00-05:00" n="870" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/743: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-03T17:00:00+09:00">June 3, 1937—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 3—7:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>145. My telegram No. 144, June 1, 10 p.m. We have just learned by
                            telephone from the Foreign Office that Hirota has accepted the Foreign
                            Affairs portfolio. The reappointment of Ministers of War and of the Navy
                            has been confirmed. Kaya, now Vice Minister of Finance, has accepted the
                            Ministry of Finance.</p>
                        <p>It is generally expected that the formation of the new Cabinet will be
                            completed before end of the day.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>